For such Iaws are not truly Laws, but rather acts of violence.

And the effective Power of Obliging is not in the Law but in the Lawgiver, and fails when he has no authority. And so Rom. xiii. 5, the Apostle says we must be subject to the Powers that be, to those who have Authority.

12. Objection 1. You may say that a mob like this has Power.

To this we answer, They have Strenyth (δύναμις), but not Authority (ἐξουσία,) upon which Obligation depends.
